Class showTracker

java.lang.Object
ece325_lab_assignment4.showTracker
public class showTracker
extends java.lang.Object
This class is designed to check the feeding history at the ZooShow. It will need a file, as well as the date we are checking to see if the animals have been fed on that date. File must be of generated format from AlreadyFedException class, and Zoo class.

  • Method Details

    • checkHistory

      public static boolean checkHistory​(java.io.File file, java.lang.String date, java.lang.Boolean debug)
      Checks given file to see if animals from ZooShow have been fed already on the given date. If the date is not found, this method will generate a header in the file for the given date so that a new list of animal records can be recorded for the date.
      Parameters:
      file - is a file that must be one generated only from this class, AlreadyFedException, and Zoo classes.
      date - is a String of the format yyyy-mm-dd which is the date that is being checked for in the file.
      debug - is used for the sake of ECE 302 assignment, it is used in order to tell this method to create a new feeding log regardless of the date given in order to test functionality accurately. (Such as marking) Set to true for marking, false for proper design functionality.
      Returns:
      true if the date is found in the file, false otherwise. It will also return false if debug is set to true.
